tobiko/openstack/stacks/_nova.py.message:
I would implement it as below:

 def validate_boot_finished(self):
     for attempt in tobiko.retry(...):
         if "login:" in self.console_output:
             break
         if attempt.is_last:
             LOG.warning(...)
             raise InvalidStackError(...)  # This will force stack recreation


InvalidStackError exception is expected to trigger stack recreation as resort. This mean when raising it, if retry creation is enabled, then the stack is deleted and recreated. This will implicitly give a second opportunity to have things right. Raising exceptions also make clear what condition is causing a problem without digging too much in the code or in log files just by reading the stack trace.

